webpackJsonp([0x642969cc376e],{1362:function(t,e){t.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Psyked.co.uk",author:"James Ford"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/James/Repositories/portfolio-2018/src/posts/tracking-flash-flex-air-applications-with-google-analytics/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>In case you weren't aware, a lot of the stuff you can do in a website you can also do in the Flash Player.  Prime example: Google Analytics tracking.</p>\n<p>Now for a simple Flash movie, you'd traditionally host the Flash file in an external website, and add the tracking to the HTML pages.  If you're doing something a little more different - or are obsessive about knowing how your users are interacting with the content - you might be interested to know that there is support for actionscript-initiated tracking, and that it's supported by Google themselves (a good sign).</p>\n<p>You can read all about the Google Analytics tracking component for Flash on the Google code website: <a href=\"http://code.google.com/apis/analytics/docs/tracking/flashTrackingIntro.html\">http://code.google.com/apis/analytics/docs/tracking/flashTrackingIntro.html</a></p>\n<p>Where this really comes into its own is in AIR applications.  Flash / Flex tracking in a HTML website isn't really all that special - once you know the API a little, you can always use the ExternalInterface commands in the Flash Player to communicate with javascript functions on the host page, but that kind of option isn't usually available to a pure Flash-based AIR application.  Using the component effectively removes the need for the external javascript file, and means that your desktop AIR application can communicate freely with Google Analytics - enabling application tracking.  The code is no different whether its an online Flash webpage, or a desktop AIR application.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"Tracking Flash / Flex / AIR applications with Google Analytics",date:"June 24, 2009",tags:["flash","flex","air","google","google-analytics"],url:null}}},pathContext:{prev:{frontmatter:{path:"/blog/tutorial-link-jquery-for-absolute-beginners/",tags:["javascript","jquery"],title:"Tutorial Link: jQuery for Absolute Beginners",image:null,date:"2009-02-24T14:21:21.000Z"}},next:{frontmatter:{path:"/blog/trouble-migrating-to-actionscript-3/",tags:["actionscript"],title:"Trouble migrating to Actionscript 3?",image:null,date:"2008-02-27T08:00:35.000Z"}}}}}});
